						               													<description>Magazine game from Jeux et Strat&amp;#195;&amp;#169;gie #4&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A simple cooperative adventure game with a basic &amp;quot;Dungeon and Dragon&amp;quot; aim : get to the castle and pillage it without being killed by various monsters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sitting between a role-playing-game and a board game, this was meant as an introductory RPG which could be played with or without a dungeon master. At the start of the game, players select a character among four classes (warrior, wizard, cleric, and thief) and chose one of four weapons (dagger, sword, club, and bow).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players make their way towards the castle either alone or as a group by moving on the game board. On this board, they step onto circle, triangle or square spaces which determine encounters through the roll of a six-sided die. No events or encounters are associated with circle spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Triangle space die roll&amp;#10;1-4: Nothing&amp;#10;5: 1 Random monster&amp;#10;6: 2 Random monsters or 1 monster and 1 treasure&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Square space die roll&amp;#10;1-3: Nothing&amp;#10;4: 1 Random monster&amp;#10;5: 2 of any random combination of monsters and treasures &amp;#10;6: 3 of any random combination of monsters and treasures&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Certain treasures can only be acquired once players have made their way inside the castle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For every monster encounter, players can either fight or flee. Both options are resolved through dice rolls.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
